Hellplague:
 
Finished with her work on the computer, she gets up and out to stretch and for a change in scenery.  With the security codes in her memory, there would be no problem of getting in if she should need to.  She stepped out and looked around for Celeron, perhaps for a little conversation or cheap entertainment.

rm2kmidi <kraftlos@...> wrote:
Celeron decides it would be best to find out if he had the material to
repair the ship before he began to patch the hull.  He decided it
would be best to fixt the big holes first, since they were greater
security risks than the smaller ones that were not likely to permit
unauthorized entry.  He began searching around for spare metal that
may have fallen off of the ship and stacked it up in the storage
room....



"HA!  Is that all you got?  You boasted such power, such skill!  Where is your power and skill now?  You disappoint me, ha ha ha haa!"
